The paper discusses neural network pruning techniques and their impact on computational performance and accuracy. This topic falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and specifically relates to neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also includes experiments on image classification tasks (MNIST and CIFAR10), which are commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) research. Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of initializations in training neural networks, which is a topic of interest in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Finally, the paper includes experiments on natural language processing tasks (GLUE benchmark), which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL).
